snippet.title: SNES Longplay [144] Fighter's History: Mizoguchi Kiki Ippatsu!!
snippet.description:

Mizoguchi Mode

Stage 02: 09:09 - Karnov
Stage 03: 12:48 - Lee
Stage 04: 15:32 - Feilin
Stage 05: 18:41 - Zazie
Stage 06: 23:01 - Yungmie
Stage 07: 26:27 - Clown
Stage 08: 29:53 - Chelnov

Fighter's History is a series of competitive fighting games that were produced by Data East during the 1990s. The original Fighter's History was first released for the arcades in 1993 and then ported to the Super Nintendo Entertainment System in 1994. Two different sequels were produced: Fighter's History Dynamite, known in Europe as Karnov's Revenge, for the Neo Geo in 1994, followed by Fighter's History: Mizoguchi Kiki Ippatsu!!, released exclusively in Japan for the Super Famicom in 1995.
